===Noun===
'''flat''' (''plural'' '''flats''')

#(''music'') A note played a [[semitone]] lower than a [[natural]], denoted by the symbol [[&#9837;]] sign placed after the letter representing the note (''eg'', B&#9837;)
#(''especially British'') An [[apartment]].
#(''colloquial'') A flat [[tyre]]/[[tire]].
#(''in plural'' '''flats''') A type of ladies' shoes with very low heels.
#:''She liked to walk in her '''flats''' more than in her high heels.''
#(''painting'') A thin, broad brush used in oil and [[watercolor]]/[[watercolour]] painting.

